Pero App - End-User License Agreement (EULA)

Last Updated: 18 Feb 2024

Welcome to Pero, the innovative app for chatting and life drawing! Before you dive into the creative community, please take a moment to review and accept our End-User License Agreement (EULA). By using the Pero app, you agree to abide by the terms and conditions outlined below.

1. No Tolerance for Objectionable Content or Abusive Users:

Pero strictly prohibits objectionable content and abusive behavior. Users engaging in such activities may face immediate account suspension or termination.
2. Filtering Objectionable Content:

Pero employs state-of-the-art content filtering algorithms to automatically detect and restrict objectionable content. This includes, but is not limited to, explicit material, hate speech, harassment, and any content violating community guidelines.
3. User-Flagging Mechanism:

Users are encouraged to actively participate in maintaining a positive and respectful community. If you come across objectionable content, please use the in-app reporting feature to flag it for review by our moderation team.

To flag content:

Navigate to the specific content.
Tap on the flag/report icon.
Provide details about the objectionable content.
Our moderation team will promptly review flagged content and take appropriate action.

4. User Blocking Mechanism:

Pero provides users with the ability to block individuals displaying abusive behavior. This feature empowers users to control their online experience and ensures a safer and more enjoyable environment.

To block a user:

Visit the user's profile.
Select the "Block User" option.
Once blocked, the user will be unable to interact with you on the platform.

Your Agreement:

By using Pero, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agreed to abide by the terms and conditions outlined in this EULA. Failure to comply with these terms may result in account suspension or termination. We are committed to fostering a positive and creative community, and your cooperation is crucial in achieving this goal.

Thank you for being a part of the Pero community! If you have any questions or concerns, please contact our support team at santosh95.freelance@gmail.com
